  "267:266": {
    "inputs": {
      "value": "Style: realistic cinematic lighting, early morning atmosphere in a narrow ancient town alley. In a medium close-up, a thin fourteen-year-old boy stands quietly beside the cracked wooden door of an old house. The door surface is peeling and worn, the threshold damp, scattered firewood leaning against the wall. The stone pavement reflects faint cold morning light and thin mist drifts slowly through the alley. The boy wears simple gray-green rough cloth clothes and worn trousers. His hair is tied in a small traditional knot. In one hand he holds a dry peach branch, and in the other he carefully protects a burning candle. The candle flame flickers softly in the cold morning air. Audio: soft morning wind passing through the alley, faint distant dog barking, subtle candle flame crackling. Phase 1 (0-3s): Medium eye-level shot. The boy stands quietly beside the door. His head is slightly lowered and his lips move softly as if whispering an old prayer. His breathing is slow and controlled. Audio: soft morning wind passing through the alley, faint distant dog barking, subtle candle flame crackling. Phase 2 (3-7s): Emotion slowly rises. His eyes become moist and a single tear slowly rolls down his cheek. His fingers tighten slightly around the candle. A small breeze enters the alley and he instinctively turns slightly to shield the candle flame. The peach branch trembles slightly in his hand. Audio: soft cloth rustling, wind brushing through the alley, faint wooden door creaking. Phase 3 (7-10s): The camera slowly pushes forward toward the boy. Tears continue to move down his face. He slowly lifts his eyes forward. His lips tremble slightly and he quietly says: “我好难过。” His voice is soft and restrained, filled with sadness. The candle flame becomes steady in his hands. Audio: gentle wind ambience, candle flame crackling, distant dog barking far away, soft emotional whisper."
    },
